Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.48,0:00:04.40,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Kogoro-no-occhan and I came to a hotel
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.58,0:00:07.31,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,to meet spirit detective Hotta Gaito.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.84,0:00:10.40,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,However, we found the man
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.55,0:00:13.56,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,we were supposed to meet \Nmurdered in a hotel room.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.91,0:00:17.67,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Not only that, but in the room next door...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.67,0:00:19.83,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Who is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.10,0:00:21.83,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,What's with all the noise?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.18,0:00:24.37,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Y-You...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.68,0:00:27.75,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.75,0:00:30.00,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,You're the guy from the detective agency.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.22,0:00:33.18,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,S-Sera... no-neechan?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.43,0:00:48.30,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Even heaven is watching the \Nlabyrinths of the world!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.30,0:00:49.98,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Full throttle reasoning skills \Npenetrate all mysteries!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.62,0:00:52.44,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Is Sera the only one living next door?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.55,0:00:54.57,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The case turns a deeper shade of black.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.86,0:00:56.53,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Always determining the one truth
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.53,0:00:58.72,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,with the body of a child \Nand the mind of an adult,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.72,0:01:01.40,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,his name is Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.00,0:02:36.02,DCEpTitle,EPTITLE,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(400,1)}The Spirit Detective's Murder \N(Part Two)
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.81,0:02:34.40,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,"The Spirit Detective's Murder, Part Two!"
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.88,0:02:39.01,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,By the way,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.41,0:02:43.35,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,did Hotta-san order this wine \Nwhile staying in this room?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.35,0:02:44.01,DCMain,BOY A,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.72,0:02:48.89,DCMain,BOY A,0000,0000,0000,,He said he was meeting someone,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.89,0:02:51.17,DCMain,BOY A,0000,0000,0000,,so I brought snacks and wine for two.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.17,0:02:52.51,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.51,0:02:56.08,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Do you have any idea who he was meeting?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.08,0:02:57.78,DCMain,KOKURI,0000,0000,0000,,No idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.61,0:03:02.78,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,It sure is hot in here.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.08,0:03:04.18,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.18,0:03:08.20,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,It's chilly today, but not cold \Nenough to turn on the heat.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.20,0:03:11.79,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,If the killer were trying to \Ndisguise the time of death,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.44,0:03:17.15,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,they would've turned up the heat \Nin the bedroom where the body is,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.15,0:03:20.80,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,but it's cold in here because \Nthe windows were left open.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.22,0:03:26.68,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Mori-kun, are you sure you saw \Nsomeone run from that window?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.17,0:03:29.43,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. I saw it with my own two eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.80,0:03:34.69,DCItalic,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Someone just ran from the balcony.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.04,0:03:39.82,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Come to think of it, there was a gust \Nof wind when we opened the door.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.99,0:03:41.55,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Wind?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.55,0:03:46.62,DCMain,KOKURI,0000,0000,0000,,That's probably because I \Nhad the front door open.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.87,0:03:52.00,Sanpei,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,1)}Kokuri Sanpei (35) \NToto TV Director
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.14,0:03:49.80,DCMain,KOKURI,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}If someone came running out of the room,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.80,0:03:52.00,DCMain,KOKURI,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}I thought I'd capture it on camera.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.17,0:03:54.75,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Why didn't you close it?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.75,0:03:57.00,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,They would've escaped.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.12,0:04:01.42,DCMain,KOKURI,0000,0000,0000,,But they'd attack me if they couldn't escape.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.70,0:04:04.18,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,I-I suppose.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.62,0:04:08.71,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe the wind blew the glasses to the floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.39,0:04:14.19,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,But the glasses fell when \Nthe front door was opened,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.44,0:04:15.94,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,before the bedroom door was opened.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.94,0:04:17.51,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Conan-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.51,0:04:18.44,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.60,0:04:22.18,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Was that bellhop here \Nwhen you found the body?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.18,0:04:22.95,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.27,0:04:28.46,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,At first it was just me, \NKogoro-no-ojisan, and Kokuri-san,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.46,0:04:31.44,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,but nobody answered when \Nwe rang the doorbell.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.08,0:04:36.00,DCItalic,KOKURI,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? That's weird.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.36,0:04:38.41,DCItalic,KOKURI,0000,0000,0000,,He should be in his room.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.80,0:04:42.55,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Then Kokuri-san noticed he received \Nan e-mail from Hotta-san
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.55,0:04:46.82,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,an hour earlier, and when he saw it...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.82,0:04:47.47,DCItalic,KOKURI,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.72,0:04:50.35,DCItalic,KOKURI,0000,0000,0000,,"Th-They're going to kill me. Help?"
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.80,0:04:55.97,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Then he went to get a bellhop \Nto unlock the door for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.83,0:04:57.97,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.97,0:05:01.22,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Was the bellhop able to unlock it right away?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.22,0:05:02.11,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.11,0:05:03.40,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,When he was about to unlock it...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.40,0:05:04.61,DCItalic,KOKURI,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.03,0:05:06.00,DCItalic,KOKURI,0000,0000,0000,,My phone's ringing.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.88,0:05:08.41,DCItalic,KOKURI,0000,0000,0000,,Hello, Hotta-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.81,0:05:10.08,DCItalic,KOKURI,0000,0000,0000,,Is that you, Hotta-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.75,0:05:11.79,DCItalic,KOKURI,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.10,0:05:13.85,DCItalic,KOKURI,0000,0000,0000,,It was a wrong number.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.85,0:05:15.46,DCItalic,BELLHOP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm opening the door.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.46,0:05:16.30,DCItalic,KOKURI,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.08,0:05:20.04,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Then when we opened the door...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.87,0:05:22.95,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Well?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.95,0:05:26.01,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Was that a clear enough explanation \Nfor your mystery person?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.16,0:05:26.78,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.22,0:05:30.34,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Who are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.34,0:05:35.78,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,More importantly, I want to see \Nwhat's above the balcony window.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.78,0:05:37.31,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,S-Sure...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.15,0:05:44.72,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,There.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.26,0:05:48.14,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,How is it, Conan-kun?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.14,0:05:51.00,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,It's a little sticky.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.33,0:05:53.20,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,As though something was stuck here.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.34,0:05:54.84,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.84,0:05:58.44,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,So you found signs something \Nwas stuck above the window.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.07,0:05:59.88,DCMain,POLICE,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, you!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.29,0:06:03.35,DCMain,POLICE,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing over there?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.35,0:06:04.46,DCMain,POLICE,0000,0000,0000,,Get off the balcony.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.09,0:06:09.64,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe something was stuck to the window,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.64,0:06:13.56,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,and set to blow away when \Nthe door was opened.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.56,0:06:18.16,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Air flows away from hot and towards cold.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.16,0:06:24.04,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,But I don't think the wind would've \Nbeen enough to unstick something.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.04,0:06:29.37,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Even if it did, the object that was \Nblown away should be around somewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.23,0:06:32.01,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.01,0:06:34.79,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,But either way,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.08,0:06:38.03,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Kokuri-san probably did it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.39,0:06:45.27,DCMain,POLICE,0000,0000,0000,,Inspector Megure, we'll be leaving now.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.05,0:06:47.57,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Good work.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.17,0:06:48.92,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Whoa!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.53,0:06:50.80,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,What is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.00,0:06:52.50,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.50,0:06:54.01,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Did you find something?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.21,0:06:55.71,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.71,0:06:57.89,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,When I went to use the bathroom,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.19,0:07:00.94,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,the toilet lid opened on \Nits own and surprised me.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.35,0:07:05.36,DCItalic,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Why's he using the bathroom at a crime scene?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.56,0:07:08.12,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,A lot of modern toilets do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.12,0:07:08.99,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.28,0:07:10.17,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.17,0:07:14.76,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,They have a sensor that opens the lid \Nautomatically when a person approaches.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.80,0:07:19.25,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,There's a sensor, and it opens automatically?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.84,0:07:22.88,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Sensor... automatically...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.76,0:07:25.35,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Sensor...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.59,0:07:31.02,DCItalic,KOKURI,0000,0000,0000,,Let's head there.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.64,0:07:36.36,DCItalic,KOKURI,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Hotta-san emailed me an hour ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.75,0:07:37.67,DCItalic,KOKURI,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.22,0:07:40.64,DCItalic,KOKURI,0000,0000,0000,,"Th-They're going to kill me. Help?"
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.12,0:07:44.69,DCItalic,KOKURI,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry. It took a while \Nto explain the situation.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.53,0:07:46.64,DCItalic,KOKURI,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.57,0:07:48.55,DCItalic,KOKURI,0000,0000,0000,,My phone's ringing.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.73,0:07:51.37,DCItalic,KOKURI,0000,0000,0000,,It was a wrong number.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.84,0:07:54.16,DCItalic,BOY A,0000,0000,0000,,Hotta-sama?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.26,0:08:00.25,DCItalic,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Someone just ran from the balcony.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.46,0:08:02.79,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,There's a car parked \Ndirectly below the balcony.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.12,0:08:04.75,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,What's it doing there?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.35,0:08:06.81,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.81,0:08:08.50,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,So that's how it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.01,0:08:11.28,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Sera-no-neechan.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.24,0:08:14.51,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,What? Deliver what?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.90,0:08:16.18,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.55,0:08:17.86,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I don't have a choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.57,0:08:20.08,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, mister.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.64,0:08:22.68,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,There's something I want to show you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.95,0:08:26.14,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,What do you want to show me?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.14,0:08:27.74,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Just come with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.74,0:08:28.81,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Sheesh.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.85,0:08:35.61,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Now that forensics is finished, \Nthere's nothing left to see.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.96,0:08:42.66,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.00,0:08:45.51,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The Sleeping Kogoro's ready to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.51,0:08:47.29,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,This'll be a little sketchy \Nsince Sera's here.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.91,0:08:50.65,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Now I just have to use my \Nbow tie-shaped voice changer
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.65,0:08:53.49,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,to produce the old man's voice and...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.15,0:08:57.14,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, what?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.58,0:08:58.51,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Crap.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.17,0:09:01.41,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,My voice changer's missing.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.92,0:09:07.23,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Crap.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.23,0:09:10.27,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I dropped my bow tie-shaped \Nvoice changer somewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.00,0:09:14.53,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The Sleeping Kogoro can't \Nsolve the case without it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.28,0:09:17.72,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I already put him to sleep, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.72,0:09:19.02,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Mori-kun?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.28,0:09:21.58,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Th-That pose. Does this mean...?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.58,0:09:23.50,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,You solved the case.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.02,0:09:27.00,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Uh, Mori-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.47,0:09:29.67,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Is he actually asleep?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.33,0:09:33.67,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,M-Maybe he's just thinking.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.06,0:09:37.18,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Why does it have to be so confusing?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.35,0:09:45.61,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Sera should be able to solve this case.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.25,0:09:45.93,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Yeah. Yeah, I got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.23,0:09:50.01,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,But she doesn't know about Kokuri-san's car.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.01,0:09:51.39,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Conan-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.31,0:09:53.90,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Want some help?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.23,0:09:55.57,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,You're in trouble, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.83,0:09:58.86,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I-I'm not in trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.20,0:10:01.12,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,How about you, Kogoro-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.12,0:10:02.37,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Do you need help?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.77,0:10:05.16,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, answer me.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.16,0:10:07.35,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,You look like you're actually asleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.35,0:10:08.50,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,H-Hey, wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.86,0:10:11.88,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Sleep is a biological function
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.21,0:10:15.76,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,of the periodically repeated \Nloss of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.11,0:10:20.51,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, it's practically impossible \Nfor a person to speak while sleeping.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.93,0:10:18.32,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}The old man's voice...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.74,0:10:22.34,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,A smartphone behind his neck?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.34,0:10:24.98,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Naturally, sleep talking is an exception.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.92,0:10:25.52,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Where did that come from?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.82,0:10:29.02,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,The words I'm speaking now must sound like
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.02,0:10:32.52,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,nonsensical sleep talking to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.30,0:10:36.18,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,But since they are the words of the detective
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.18,0:10:40.03,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,who has solved this ridiculous \Ncase, I ask that you listen.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.99,0:10:42.91,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}You really did solve the case.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.15,0:10:42.38,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,That's it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.38,0:10:44.80,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,She must be using my voice changer \Nfrom behind the curtains.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.91,0:10:45.16,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}But you're speaking differently than usual.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.37,0:10:46.33,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.69,0:10:50.87,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Don't get in the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.55,0:10:56.63,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I prefer to be brief, \Nso I'll start at the end.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.27,0:11:00.94,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,The man who murdered spirit detective Hotta,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.39,0:11:08.64,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,and made it seem as though \Nthe killer fled the scene
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.64,0:11:11.90,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,when we arrived, is TV director Kokuri.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.72,0:11:21.11,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,B-But you said the wine glasses and plates \Nfell when you opened the front door,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.11,0:11:23.91,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,so you followed their wine-soaked footsteps,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.91,0:11:27.15,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,and saw someone running
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.15,0:11:32.33,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,from the balcony when you \Nopened the bedroom door.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.61,0:11:36.68,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,There was construction taking place \Non the floor below when it happened,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.68,0:11:38.99,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,so the room was shaking slightly,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.99,0:11:41.66,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,but the odds the utensils \Nwould've fallen were 50-50,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.66,0:11:43.59,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,so it couldn't have been used as a trick.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.85,0:11:46.10,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,No, it was 100%.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.69,0:11:49.35,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,It was impossible for them not to fall.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.37,0:11:52.84,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,I-Impossible?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.84,0:11:54.00,DCMain,BOY B,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.00,0:11:54.73,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.23,0:11:59.75,DCMain,BOY B,0000,0000,0000,,I brought a wine glass, a bottle \Nof wine, a plate, and salt.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.75,0:12:02.61,DCMain,BOY B,0000,0000,0000,,Detective Mori said he needed \Nthem for the investigation.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.02,0:12:04.11,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.33,0:12:11.58,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,First, set the plate on \Nthe very edge of the table.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.58,0:12:16.62,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Then pour a large amount of salt next to \Nthe plate towards the center of the table.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.62,0:12:17.63,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.32,0:12:21.63,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,I poured the salt.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.01,0:12:24.58,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Then put the wine glass on top of the salt
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.96,0:12:27.64,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,so it's leaning towards the plate.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.25,0:12:30.64,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Put the wine glass...leaning...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.30,0:12:32.42,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,I put the wine glass on the—
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.42,0:12:35.30,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Once the glass is on the \Ntable, blow the salt away.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.90,0:12:38.48,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Just weakly enough that \Nthe glass doesn't fall.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.42,0:12:43.45,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,That's amazing.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.00,0:12:45.45,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,It's still standing.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.45,0:12:46.34,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.34,0:12:51.20,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,The glass is being held up \Nby just a few grains of salt.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.88,0:12:57.32,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Finally, place the bottle against the \Nbase of the glass and shake the table.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.28,0:13:01.84,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,The glass becomes unbalanced, \Nand the bottle blocks its fall,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.84,0:13:04.27,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,forcing it to fall towards the plate.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.27,0:13:07.82,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,The glass and plate fall \Non the floor together.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.40,0:13:13.99,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,If you place broken plates and \Nglasses under the table beforehand,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.99,0:13:17.83,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,the falling objects will break and \Nmake a noise when they strike them.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.02,0:13:21.36,DCItalic,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,What was that sound?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.66,0:13:23.30,DCItalic,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,It sounded like something breaking.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.86,0:13:25.92,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,By spilling wine on the floor
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.92,0:13:29.54,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,and creating wine-stained footprints \Nleading to the bedroom,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.98,0:13:34.58,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,you made it appear as though the \Nkiller ran into the bedroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.16,0:13:38.24,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Furthermore, you created a \Ndifference in temperature
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.24,0:13:40.71,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,between this room and the \Nbedroom by turning on the heat,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.18,0:13:45.46,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,so when the bedroom door was opened, \Na breeze would blow through,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.46,0:13:49.34,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,scattering the small piles \Nof salt left on the table.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.97,0:13:54.54,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,You feared your trick would be discovered \Nif the police found piles of salt
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.54,0:13:59.86,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,with indentations left by \Nthe bottoms of the glasses.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.03,0:14:01.60,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Th-That's it!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.60,0:14:06.61,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,He used that breeze to blow \Naway whatever was stuck
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.92,0:14:10.24,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,to the window to make it \Nlook like someone ran away.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.24,0:14:10.24,Wind,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Wind
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.69,0:14:12.25,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Are you an idiot?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.58,0:14:13.95,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Think about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.38,0:14:17.65,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Wind alone wouldn't be \Nenough to blow away
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.65,0:14:20.25,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,an object stuck to the window.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.77,0:14:23.77,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Even if it did come off,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.77,0:14:28.96,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,are you saying the object disappeared \Nwithout being seen by anyone?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.96,0:14:31.39,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,How did he do it, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.39,0:14:34.26,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,There was fishing line attached to the door.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.94,0:14:38.27,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,It was attached in a way that would \Ncome undone when I opened it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.64,0:14:45.04,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,He attached a piece of fabric \Nthe same color as the curtains
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.04,0:14:47.15,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,to the bedroom window and ran \Nthe fishing line to the door.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.58,0:14:50.69,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,He taped it in place on the \Nbalcony side of the window.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.69,0:14:54.06,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Then he attached a weight to the other end
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.06,0:14:56.41,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,of the fishing line and hung \Nit from the balcony railing.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.96,0:14:59.47,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,When the door was opened and \Nthe fishing line came undone,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.80,0:15:02.28,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,the weight dragged the fabric down.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.63,0:15:06.42,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,It's a stupid trick for making \Npeople believe they saw
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.60,0:15:07.84,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,someone run across the balcony.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.29,0:15:13.22,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,But wouldn't someone have \Nfound the fallen fabric?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.22,0:15:14.49,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Masumi.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.49,0:15:15.84,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Masumi?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.84,0:15:17.85,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I doubt you saw it,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.43,0:15:21.83,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,but Kokuri parked his car \Ndirectly below the balcony.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.20,0:15:24.78,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,His convertible car.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.02,0:15:27.78,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,The switch for opening and closing
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.78,0:15:31.73,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,the roof can be attached \Nto the keys upon request.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.36,0:15:36.06,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,If the keys were attached \Nto the weight hanging
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.41,0:15:39.33,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,from the balcony with \Nthe button taped down,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.83,0:15:50.88,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,then the car's roof would have \Nclosed when the fabric fell,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.52,0:15:55.39,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,leaving only a car parked \Nin a strange location.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.06,0:16:00.98,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Additionally, this trick only works if \NI entered the room at exactly 9 AM,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.24,0:16:04.44,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,when construction began.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.89,0:16:10.15,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,That's why he set his phone to \Ngo off one minute before nine.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.89,0:16:12.01,DCMain,KOKURI,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.09,0:16:14.05,DCItalic,KOKURI,0000,0000,0000,,My phone's ringing.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.93,0:16:16.45,DCItalic,KOKURI,0000,0000,0000,,Hello, Hotta-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.87,0:16:17.89,DCItalic,KOKURI,0000,0000,0000,,Is that you, Hotta-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.86,0:16:19.83,DCItalic,KOKURI,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.22,0:16:21.83,DCItalic,KOKURI,0000,0000,0000,,It was a wrong number.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.13,0:16:23.88,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,It allowed him
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.88,0:16:28.80,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,to control the moment the bellhop \Nunlocked the door using the master key.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.36,0:16:34.29,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,If the victim's request for \Nhelp was sent an hour earlier,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.29,0:16:36.66,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,then he most likely murdered him then, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.25,0:16:41.08,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,In a country where earthquakes \Nare so frequent,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.08,0:16:43.81,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,that salt trick can't \Nbe left alone for hours.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.41,0:16:48.32,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Which means they should still be in his car.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.85,0:16:50.98,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Both the weight and fabric \Nhe used in his trick,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.41,0:16:53.82,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,as well as the weapon he used to murder Hotta
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.18,0:16:57.32,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,and clothes covered in his blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.22,0:17:00.40,DCMain,KOKURI,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.24,0:17:05.58,DCMain,KOKURI,0000,0000,0000,,The bloodstained clothes are \Nstill in the trunk of my car.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.80,0:17:10.47,DCMain,KOKURI,0000,0000,0000,,Along with the knife I used \Nto inflict retribution
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.47,0:17:13.09,DCMain,KOKURI,0000,0000,0000,,on the man who made a show \Nout of my sister's body.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.41,0:17:15.22,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Your sister's body?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.65,0:17:19.85,DCMain,KOKURI,0000,0000,0000,,Several years ago, my sister \Ncommitted suicide in the mountains.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.31,0:17:23.20,DCMain,KOKURI,0000,0000,0000,,In her note she said she \Nwas going to hang herself
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.20,0:17:25.47,DCMain,KOKURI,0000,0000,0000,,because she couldn't bear her broken heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.02,0:17:29.45,DCMain,KOKURI,0000,0000,0000,,No matter how much we searched for \Nher, we couldn't find the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.86,0:17:30.61,DCMain,KOKURI,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.28,0:17:34.86,DCMain,KOKURI,0000,0000,0000,,During a TV show, Hotta Gaito \Nsaid he sensed the death
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.13,0:17:39.12,DCMain,KOKURI,0000,0000,0000,,of someone other than the missing \Nperson on that mountain.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.78,0:17:43.12,DCMain,KOKURI,0000,0000,0000,,They discovered my sister's body in the dirt.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.76,0:17:45.50,DCMain,KOKURI,0000,0000,0000,,Do you understand?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.92,0:17:50.00,DCMain,KOKURI,0000,0000,0000,,Even though he found the \Nhanging body of my sister,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.00,0:17:53.42,DCMain,KOKURI,0000,0000,0000,,he buried it without telling the police!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.31,0:17:57.88,DCMain,KOKURI,0000,0000,0000,,All so he could make people believe \Nin his supernatural abilities!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.34,0:18:02.56,DCMain,KOKURI,0000,0000,0000,,S-So I... I...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.75,0:18:08.23,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.96,0:18:11.20,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,She went back to their room.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.64,0:18:15.21,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,You can tell us the rest at the station.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.21,0:18:16.61,DCMain,KOKURI,0000,0000,0000,,Not yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.40,0:18:18.74,DCMain,KOKURI,0000,0000,0000,,I have to tell her.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.35,0:18:21.22,DCMain,KOKURI,0000,0000,0000,,I need to visit my sister's grave,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.22,0:18:25.75,DCMain,KOKURI,0000,0000,0000,,and tell her I got the man \Nwho disgraced her death.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.46,0:18:27.78,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,H-Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.88,0:18:31.38,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.75,0:18:32.86,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.12,0:18:35.51,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Crap. He went next door.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.08,0:18:40.72,DCMain,KOKURI,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-Who are you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.85,0:18:49.00,DCMain,KOKURI,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.00,0:18:50.48,DCMain,KOKURI,0000,0000,0000,,Move!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.62,0:18:57.59,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I-Is he dead?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.44,0:19:03.41,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,No, they struck his vitals \Nand knocked him unconscious
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.28,0:19:06.60,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,during the seconds it \Ntook for me to run here.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.35,0:19:10.14,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,They're as quick as a secret service agent.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.94,0:19:15.04,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Whoever did this must have been...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.55,0:19:16.42,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Mom!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.59,0:19:17.26,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.61,0:19:18.98,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Uh, nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.98,0:19:21.78,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,A-Are you okay, Conan-kun?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.78,0:19:22.80,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.76,0:19:25.71,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Mom?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.74,0:19:32.81,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Way to go, Mom.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.17,0:19:35.68,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,It took you no time at all to learn
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.68,0:19:38.35,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,how to use Conan-kun's bow tie device.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.35,0:19:42.32,DCMain,SISTER,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, there were marks on the dials.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.97,0:19:46.33,DCMain,SISTER,0000,0000,0000,,He must've used that detective's voice often.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.66,0:19:49.99,DCMain,SISTER,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, I'm surprised he can \Nproduce all kinds of voices
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.99,0:19:53.23,DCMain,SISTER,0000,0000,0000,,with such a simple device.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.68,0:19:57.08,DCMain,SISTER,0000,0000,0000,,I could imagine using it \Nin all sorts of situations.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.08,0:19:58.82,DCMain,SISTER,0000,0000,0000,,How exciting.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.45,0:20:03.40,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.72,0:20:06.16,DCItalic,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,You don't look that excited.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.16,0:20:06.94,DCMain,SISTER,0000,0000,0000,,Well?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.43,0:20:10.74,DCMain,SISTER,0000,0000,0000,,Did you figure out what \Ninformation Hotta acquired?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.74,0:20:11.98,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.18,0:20:15.77,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Kokuri mentioned something \Nbefore he was escorted away.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.09,0:20:22.36,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Someone saw the missing bodyguard \NAsaka holding that hand mirror.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.64,0:20:26.72,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Apparently Kokuri learned Asaka was a woman.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.72,0:20:29.27,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,He planned to summon the spirit \Nof Haneda Koji and scream,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.27,0:20:34.50,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,"A woman! A woman's going to kill me!"
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.07,0:20:36.55,DCMain,SISTER,0000,0000,0000,,That's all?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.55,0:20:37.83,DCMain,SISTER,0000,0000,0000,,Ridiculous.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.83,0:20:39.63,DCMain,SISTER,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, pack your things.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.09,0:20:41.38,DCMain,SISTER,0000,0000,0000,,We're moving.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.38,0:20:42.76,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,What? Already?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.76,0:20:47.14,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,I was just thinking how lucky we are that \NConan-kun knows where we're staying.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.07,0:20:51.81,DCMain,SISTER,0000,0000,0000,,All sorts of monsters lurk in the dark.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.25,0:20:54.48,DCMain,SISTER,0000,0000,0000,,Keep your guard up around Edogawa Conan.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.87,0:20:59.60,DCMain,SISTER,0000,0000,0000,,He's nothing like the boy \Nwe met ten years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.58,0:21:01.63,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.76,0:22:27.03,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Asaka was a bodyguard and a woman.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.61,0:22:31.91,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,If she's Rum, the number two \Nperson of the Black Organization,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.22,0:22:35.74,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,then does that mean Haibara's \Ndescription of a feminine man
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.74,0:22:39.67,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,actually refers to a woman who's \Nstrong on the inside like a man?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.56,0:22:43.38,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,If she was working as a \Nbodyguard seventeen years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.38,0:22:46.17,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,then she should be pretty old by now.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.56,0:22:51.33,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,But if they returned to middle school \Nage by taking the same drug I was given,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.92,0:22:53.18,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,then the most suspicious person
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.68,0:22:57.68,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,is this girl Sera called "Mom."
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.90,0:23:00.49,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Who is she?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.92,0:23:09.95,DCMain,VODKA,0000,0000,0000,,By the way, bro, apparently Hotta Gaito,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.29,0:23:14.42,DCMain,VODKA,0000,0000,0000,,the man investigating the \NHaneda Koji murder case, died.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.70,0:23:19.96,DCMain,GIN,0000,0000,0000,,I don't care about Rum's \Nseventeen year old mistakes.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.42,0:23:23.71,DCMain,GIN,0000,0000,0000,,I'm more interested in the Sleeping Kogoro.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.85,0:23:29.97,DCMain,GIN,0000,0000,0000,,I heard he was involved in \Nthis morning's case, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.85,0:23:33.51,DCMain,GIN,0000,0000,0000,,All sorts of monsters lurk in the dark.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.08,0:23:35.66,DCMain,GIN,0000,0000,0000,,And if he's a monster,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.15,0:23:38.80,DCMain,GIN,0000,0000,0000,,then we'd better finish him \Noff while he's still asleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.98,0:24:09.01,DCEpPreview,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Episode Preview
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.82,0:23:47.86,DCMain,MAN,0000,0000,0000,,Call the police!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.14,0:23:50.36,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,What? You let them get away?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.76,0:23:53.49,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,You idiot! Don't bother coming!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.72,0:23:54.83,DCMain,WOMAN,0000,0000,0000,,The missus...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.17,0:23:56.05,DCMain,MAN,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.39,0:24:01.00,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,What kind of party is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.18,0:24:05.50,DCItalic,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Which one of those three murdered Naoko-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.89,0:24:09.01,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,That's it.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.01,0:24:15.01,DCNextEp,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,The Foul-Mouthed Myna Bird
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.74,0:24:13.72,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The next episode of Conan is \N"The Foul-Mouthed Myna Bird!"
